  "message": "chore(tests): remove stale .rebuild-failed recovery artifacts from interrupted_rebuild_leftovers fixture\n\nRemove 4 synthetic .rebuild-failed recovery files from the\ninterrupted_rebuild_leftovers workspace failure test fixture:\n\n- .beads/.br_recovery/beads.db.20260312T000000Z.rebuild-failed\n- .beads/.br_recovery/beads.db-wal.20260312T000000Z.rebuild-failed\n- beads/.br_recovery/beads.db.20260312T000000Z.rebuild-failed\n- beads/.br_recovery/beads.db-wal.20260312T000000Z.rebuild-failed\n\nThese files were timestamped recovery snapshots (database + WAL)\ncreated as part of the rebuild failure test fixture setup. They have\nbeen cleaned up as part of ongoing test fixture refactoring, likely\nbecause the test now uses a different mechanism for simulating\ninterrupted rebuilds or the fixture layout was simplified.\n\nEphemeral SQLite sidecar files (*.db-shm, *.db-wal) in\nsample_beads_db_files/ are intentionally not committed.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>",
